desc.paragraph:
HSHacks2024 website submission that was awarded 2nd place.
TaskMap is a platform that connects teens in need of volunteering opportunities to elderly people who can't do certain tasks and jobs around the house. It is heavily based on the idea of high school juniors needing volunteering hours for joining organizations such as the National Honors Society (NHS).
We used the Google Maps API to display geographical data of jobs on the website.

desc.paragraph:
Music playing website utilizing the Youtube library with a Spotify-like setup as well as local storage capabilities. Made during my time at Code Nation in Fellowship 1.
A youtube API is needed from the google developer page to use the site (which there is a guide for on the site).
Currently planned to be redone in react.

note.text: Couldn't been done without Saad. Thanks a lot!
